DESCRIPTION:Image Credits: Simi Mary\nTurn your waste materials into something beautiful!\n\nIn this weaving workshop\, participants learn the basics of weaving using different types of looms\, including circular looms\, frame looms\, and branch weaving. Most materials are sourced from waste cloth\, encouraging sustainability and creative reuse\, while wool and threads are used to explore varied textures and patterns.\n\nParticipants are also invited to bring their own waste fabric to integrate into their work. \n\nThis event is held in conjunction with our exhibition\, mild tooth of milk\, currently on display at the Dutch Warehouse in Fort Kochi.
DTEND:20260329T093000Z
DTSTART:20260329T053000Z
