ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Website-cover-images-new-2026-03-24T094726.208.png
CATEGORIES:Panel Discussion,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260324T111043Z
DESCRIPTION:Image Credits: Anoushka\nAs monuments erode and archives fade\, digital technologies including 3D scanning and immersive reconstructions offer new ways to safeguard cultural heritage. But what do we gain\, and what might we lose? Bringing together historians and conservationists\, this conversation explores how heritage is documented\, restored\, and reinterpreted today.\n\nAt the heart of it lies a harder question: in digitising the past\, do we preserve it — or reshape it?
DTEND:20260328T130000Z
DTSTART:20260328T120000Z
SUMMARY:Preserving the Past in a Digital Age
UID:1224@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/preserving-the-past-in-a-digital-age/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Website-cover-images-new-2026-03-27T090031.779.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260327T101204Z
DESCRIPTION:A safe space for trans and non-binary folks to come together and speak openly about their anxieties and feelings around the Transgender Persons (Protection of Rights) Amendment Bill\, 2026.\n\nSchedule\n\n11:00 am – 1:00 pm\nA guided check-in to reflect on how our bodies and emotions are holding this moment\, connect with what we need\, and try to access grounding amidst the challenges. Facilitated by Ananya and Sanjay\, counselling psychologists.\n\n1:00 pm – 1:45 pm\nBreak\n\n1:45 pm – 3:30 pm\nDoodling as an art form and grounding practice\, facilitated by Debbie Das—artist\, designer\, and transgender rights advocate.\n\nRegistration is compulsory. This event is exclusively for members of the queer community.\n\nThis event is in partnership with All Sorts of Queer.\n\n&nbsp\;
DTEND:20260328T100000Z
DTSTART:20260328T053000Z
